-- Former Gambian Defense Chief Is Among Eight Facing Execution, Point Says
-- Consolatah Lucas
-- 2010-07-16T05:53:17Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/former-gambian-defense-chief-is-among-eight-facing-execution-point-says.html

          
          
             The eight  Gambians  sentenced to
death for their role in an attempt to oust President  Yahya Jammeh  include the West African nationâ€™s former chief of defense
staff,  The Point  reported.  
 Lt. Gen. Lang Tambong Tamba was convicted and sentenced
yesterday by High Court Judge Emmanuel Amadi, the Banjul-based
newspaper said. Others facing the death penalty include Brig.
Gen. Omar Bun Mbye, Col. Lamin Bo Badjie, Lt. Col. Kawsu Camara,
Gibril Ngorr Secka, a former diplomat, and businessman Yousef
Ezzideen, who is also known as Rambo, it said.  
 The eight were charged with three counts of treason and all
of them pleaded not guilty, the newspaper said. They are alleged
to have acquired arms and ammunition and hired mercenaries last
year with the intention of staging a coup, it said.  
